data.api_docs:
Method: POST
Endpoint: /update/SLItems

Headers:

X-Infor-MongooseConfig: <YOUR_SITE>
Query Parameter:

refresh: true
Body:
The body of the request contains the item details in the Changes array. Below is the structure of the body:

{
  "IDOName": "SLItems",
  "RefreshAfterSave": true,
  "Changes": [
    {
      "Action": 1,
      "Properties": [
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "Item",
          "Value": "{item}" // Dynamic value that should be replaced by the agent based on the item being checked.
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "UM",
          "Value": "EA"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "MatlType",
          "Value": "M"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "PMTCode",
          "Value": "M"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "ProductCode",
          "Value": "FG-100"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "AbcCode",
          "Value": "B"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "CostType",
          "Value": "A"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "CostMethod",
          "Value": "S"
        },
        {
          "IsNull": false,
          "Modified": true,
          "Name": "Stat",
          "Value": "A"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
NOTE: The "Value" for "Item" is dynamic and should be replaced by the agent with the actual item being processed. For this tool, the agent dynamically assigns the value based on the list of items it is checking, and {item} is a variable placeholder.

data.responseInstructions:
Success Response: If the item is successfully created, the API returns the following response. The RefreshItems array contains details about the newly created item, including its unique ItemId and the properties associated with the item.
Example Success Response:

